SPAIN DAYBOOK: Cabinet Meets; Euro Finance Chiefs in Budapest

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-04-08T05:58:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/spain-daybook-cabinet-meets-euro-finance-chiefs-in-budapest.html
Euro-region finance ministers meet
in Budapest after Portugal requested a European bailout while
the Spanish Cabinet holds a weekly meeting in Madrid.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Cabinet meeting, followed by news conference by Deputy Prime
Minister Alfredo Perez Rubalcaba at 1:45 p.m. CET.  ECONOMY: *European Central Bank President Jean-Claude Trichet
said in an interview on Dutch broadcaster NOS that “countries
which are in difficulty have an interest in the stability and
solid anchoring of expectations” of prices.
*HSBC Plc Chief Economist  Stephen King  said more debt-striken
euro nations may need financial assistance after Portugal became
the third member of the bloc to seek fiscal support.  EQUITIES:
* Abertis Infraestructuras SA (ABE)  hired AZ Capital to advise it on
the sale of its Saba Infraestructuras parking and logistics
unit, Expansion reported, citing unidentified people familiar
with the matter.
* Acciona SA (ANA)  said it signed a syndicated loan for 1.42 billion
euros to refinance a loan signed in 2009 for the acquisition of
renewable energy assets from  Endesa SA. (ELE)  The margin on the 18-
year project-finance loan is 275 basis points in the first
years, rising to 350 basis points over six-month Euribor, the
company said in a regulatory filing.
*Patentes Talgo SA, Spain’s biggest railway carriage maker by
sales, hired banking advisers to prepare for a Madrid stock-
market listing that may value the company at as much as 1
billion euros ($1.4 billion), the Financial Times reported,
citing unidentified people briefed on the plans.  MARKETS:
*The  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  rose less than 0.1 percent to 10,849.1.
*The spread between Spanish and German 10-year borrowing costs
widened to 182 basis points.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at   acullen8@bloomberg.net  